  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e24" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Special resolution defined</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>For the purposes of section 16 (4) (c) of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96180_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Health Authorities Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, a special resolution for the Royal Inland Hospital, incorporated under <in:doc>An Act to Incorporate the Royal Inland Hospital</in:doc>, is defined as an approval by a majority of the voting members of the corporation present at a meeting of the membership of the corporation, called for the purpose of approving the amalgamation.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96180_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Health Authorities Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 180, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: sectionÂ 21]</reg:provisionsnote>
